track_notes: This is a very beautiful but somewhat challenging hike.  After a short section of The Arizona Trail, turn off to head towards Sycamore Reservoir.  On the way out it is mostly downhill to the Reservoir, which is a hidden gem in the Catalinas.  Several main water runoffs collect there and continue downward to Sabino Canyon.  Eventually you turn to skirt along below the cliffs that guard 5420.  On my first attempt at this summit, the cliffs won and I aborted.  This time I hiked further up to the saddle North of Thimble Peak.  There are grassy ramps on the East side below the cliffs.  I found numerous short animal paths (likely mountain lion) and gradually climbed up.  At the top are two summit blocks.  The views of Thimble Peak and the entire Catalina range are spectacular. I hiked after a couple of days of rain, so the grass and weeds were gentler and tramped down easily, but I do recommend gaitors and do NOT do this hike in hot weather.  Note, total climb was 2,500 feet overall.
